  "body": "# ðŸ¦„ Feature Tracking\r\n\r\n**Current status** (opt-in or opt-out): \r\n\r\n**Opt-in feature flag name**:\r\n\r\n**Opt-out feature flag name**: \r\n\r\n### Feature Description\r\nThe feature will allow users to enable and disable via command lines one or many validator keys.\r\nDisabled validators will not be removed from the account wallet, but instead simply be inactive and will not perform any attestation, aggregation or block proposals.\r\n\r\nThis is particularly handy if a user is looking to migrate his keys to other clients or another server without having to `delete` and `import` again his keys.\r\n\r\n### Tasks\r\n- [x] Feature to disable accounts for imported accounts (#7746)\r\n- [x] Feature to enable accounts for imported accounts(#7746)\r\n- [ ] Distinguish disabled accounts from active ones (`accounts list`)\r\n- [ ] Feature to disable accounts for derived accounts \r\n- [ ] Feature to enable accounts for derived accounts \r\n- [ ] `enable` and `disable` should have effect without requiring the user to restart their validator node\r\n\r\nThis issue should be closed after all of the above tasks are complete.\r\n",
